%F A001414 If n = Product p_j^k_j then a(n) = Sum p_j * k_j.
%F A001414 Dirichlet g.f. f(s)*zeta(s), where f(s) = Sum_{p prime} p/(p^s-1) = Sum_{k>0} primezeta(k*s-1) is the Dirichlet g.f. for A120007. Totally additive with a(p^e) = p*e. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Jun 02 2006
%F A001414 For n > 1: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..A001222(n)} A027746(n,k). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 27 2011
%F A001414 Sum_{n>=1} (-1)^a(n)/n^s = ((2^s + 1)/(2^s - 1))*zeta(2*s)/zeta(s), if Re(s)>1 and 0 if s=1 (Alladi and Erdős, 1977). - _Amiram Eldar_, Nov 02 2020
%F A001414 a(n) >= k*log(n), where k = 3/log(3). This bound is sharp. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 28 2025
%e A001414 a(24) = 2+2+2+3 = 9.
%e A001414 a(30) = 10: 30 can be written as 30, 15*2, 10*3, 6*5, 5*3*2. The corresponding sums are 30, 17, 13, 11, 10. Among these 10 is the least.
